Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Viagra at Scoreblue. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Hi, how's it going? Can you guys look up my account? I have—

Speaker 2: And I haven't received anything yet.

Speaker 2: Can I get your full name and date of birth?

Speaker 1: Yeah, Tim McDuffie, M-C-D-U-F-F-I-E, 12-21-1967.

Speaker 1: So, Tim, I'm looking at your prescription.

Speaker 2: It looks like you called in back in September—

Speaker 1: And placed an order for the 100 milligram Viagra AGV,

Speaker 2: and I believe that was the refill that went through.

Speaker 1: That's why you saw that charge.

Speaker 1: Yeah, Cialis. Do you guys still sell those?

Speaker 1: Yeah. I prefer, actually, I've tried both now, and I think I like the Cialis better.

Speaker 2: I would rather do a, what was I doing a while ago back?

Speaker 1: I was spending like $150 every five, six months.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so those were a lower dose Cialis.

Speaker 2: Do you have a higher Cialis these days?

Speaker 1: 20-milligram, you mean quantity or milligram dosage?

Speaker 2: Milligram.

Speaker 1: 20 milligrams is legally the largest milligram dosage they can do that's FDA approved,

Speaker 2: so they don't make anything bigger than 20.

Speaker 1: Okay, because you were just saying I was getting a lower dosage.

Speaker 2: Lower dosage?

Speaker 1: Did you say that, or was I, I was getting a 20, wasn't I?

Speaker 2: You were getting 24 of 20 milligrams of the Cialis.

Speaker 1: What was I, and I was getting 24, how many months at a time was I getting that?

Speaker 2: You were getting that every three months.

Speaker 1: Can we go back to that? I like that, the yellow pill, way better than the one you guys sent me.

Speaker 2: Okay. Yeah, let me go ahead and adjust this, so we'll go ahead and do the generic daily Cialis.

Speaker 1: And how much does that cost?

Speaker 2: Thank you for your help.

Speaker 1: Of course.

Speaker 2: I tried those out, and, you know, they made me feel kind of weird.

Speaker 1: I think my body's used to the Cialis.

Speaker 2: So yeah, I can honor your, the same pricing here.

Speaker 1: So that would be 24, 20 milligram Cialis at 159.

Speaker 2: For every three months.

Speaker 1: Yep.

Speaker 2: Let me use the ones you sent today.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So it's end of January, so February, March, so what, end of April, send me, do that deal?

Speaker 1: So when I change your prescription over, it will put an order in.

Speaker 2: So I would just, yeah, so if you want that at a later date, I would advise you give us a call.

Speaker 1: Otherwise, I could place the order today.

Speaker 2: If I place the order today, it would change the script over, but that order would go through.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So then leave it as is, and then I'll call back, and when I'm ready, I'll call you guys back.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Perfect.

Speaker 1: That sounds fine.

Speaker 2: And if you could cancel that five-month thing.

Speaker 1: Okay, yeah.

Speaker 2: Five months.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: And I'll just cancel it.

Speaker 1: I'll call back soon.

Speaker 2: I did have a bunch of them stocked up, and I am starting to get low.

Speaker 1: So those are the ones I like, and those are the ones I want to get.

Speaker 2: So let me look at how many I have left, and then we'll go from there.

Speaker 1: Okay, you got it.

Speaker 2: You got it.

Speaker 1: I'm taking notes here that you're going to call back here in a few months to adjust it

Speaker 2: over to the Cialis.

Speaker 1: Yeah, yeah.

Speaker 2: Get rid of that other one completely.

Speaker 1: I still have a few left.

Speaker 2: And you know what I do?

Speaker 1: I go to the Cialis every time, because those white ones that you guys sent me, they're—

Speaker 2: a lot stronger, and they made me kind of feel weird.

Speaker 1: Oh, interesting.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Like I said, I think my body's just used to that.

Speaker 2: Sure.

Speaker 1: Everyone's different.

Speaker 2: Everybody's different.

Speaker 1: So I appreciate it, and cancel that, and I'll call back, and I'll see how many I have left.

Speaker 2: Okay, you got it.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Well, I was just wondering what was going on.

Speaker 1: So thank you so much.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.

Speaker 1: Happy to help.

Speaker 2: Have a good day.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.

Speaker 1: Bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.

Speaker 1: Bye.
